<subSubSection id="C36B651CFFC2FF88FF154C11FB6EFCEE" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BCE3697FFC2FF88FF154C11FB6EFCEE" blockId="14.[151,1436,591,1700]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis id="B905EA85FFC2FF88FF154C11FE94FDAC" bold="true" box="[151,282,591,617]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D14FFC2FF88FDC04C0EFD7BFDAC" authorityName="Bosenberg &amp; Strand" authorityYear="1906" box="[578,757,592,617]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crypticolens">
<emphasis id="B905EA85FFC2FF88FDC04C0EFD7BFDAC" box="[578,757,592,617]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">P. crypticolens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D14FFC2FF88FC874C0EFC0BFDAC" box="[773,901,592,617]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="manueli">
<emphasis id="B905EA85FFC2FF88FC874C0EFC0BFDAC" box="[773,901,592,617]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">P. manueli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D14FFC2FF88FC434C0EFBAEFDAC" authorityName="Zhu &amp; Gong" authorityYear="1991" box="[961,1056,592,617]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spilis">
<emphasis id="B905EA85FFC2FF88FC434C0EFBAEFDAC" box="[961,1056,592,617]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">P. spilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, probably near relatives, in the shape of the palpal bulb, all with broad, almost triangular appendices; all femora of male palps with a dorsal projection retrolaterally; all epigyna with large pore plates. 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D14FFC2FF88FCCE4CC3FC3BFD73" authorityName="Zhu &amp; Gong" authorityYear="1991" box="[844,949,669,694]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bessus">
<emphasis id="B905EA85FFC2FF88FCCE4CC3FC3BFD73" box="[844,949,669,694]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">P. bessus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D14FFC2FF88FB724CC3FA12FD73" authorityName="Bosenberg &amp; Strand" authorityYear="1906" box="[1264,1436,669,694]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crypticolens">
<emphasis id="B905EA85FFC2FF88FB724CC3FA12FD73" box="[1264,1436,669,694]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">P. crypticolens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D14FFC2FF88FF4A4C9AFEACFD18" authorityName="Zhu &amp; Gong" authorityYear="1991" box="[200,290,708,733]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spilis">
<emphasis id="B905EA85FFC2FF88FF4A4C9AFEACFD18" box="[200,290,708,733]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">P. spilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the shape of tip of the procursus (
<figureCitation id="134A2A12FFC2FF88FD564C9AFCD3FD1B" box="[724,861,708,734]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="15.[151,255,1887,1911]" captionTargetBox="[256,1339,226,1852]" captionTargetId="figure-78@15.[244,1352,194,1880]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 3. Pholcus bessus Zhu &amp; Gong, 1991 (illustrations modified from Zhu &amp; Gong 1991). A. epigynum, ventral view. B. same, dorsal view. C. male prosoma, dorsal view. D. trochanter of male left palp, retrolaterodorsal view. E. male left chelicera, frontal view. F. left palp, prolateral view. G. same, retrolateral view. Scale lines: 1.0mm (C), 0.5mm (A, B, E–G), 0.2mm (D)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5317618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5317618/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Figs. 3F–G</figureCitation>
), by the broad V-shape of the anterior sclerotized arch of epigynum (
<figureCitation id="134A2A12FFC2FF88FE014CB4FE6AFCC1" box="[387,484,746,772]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="15.[151,255,1887,1911]" captionTargetBox="[256,1339,226,1852]" captionTargetId="figure-78@15.[244,1352,194,1880]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 3. Pholcus bessus Zhu &amp; Gong, 1991 (illustrations modified from Zhu &amp; Gong 1991). A. epigynum, ventral view. B. same, dorsal view. C. male prosoma, dorsal view. D. trochanter of male left palp, retrolaterodorsal view. E. male left chelicera, frontal view. F. left palp, prolateral view. G. same, retrolateral view. Scale lines: 1.0mm (C), 0.5mm (A, B, E–G), 0.2mm (D)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5317618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5317618/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
), and by the carapace with butterfly-shaped central marks (
<figureCitation id="134A2A12FFC2FF88FB4A4CB4FAA7FCC1" box="[1224,1321,746,772]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="15.[151,255,1887,1911]" captionTargetBox="[256,1339,226,1852]" captionTargetId="figure-78@15.[244,1352,194,1880]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 3. Pholcus bessus Zhu &amp; Gong, 1991 (illustrations modified from Zhu &amp; Gong 1991). A. epigynum, ventral view. B. same, dorsal view. C. male prosoma, dorsal view. D. trochanter of male left palp, retrolaterodorsal view. E. male left chelicera, frontal view. F. left palp, prolateral view. G. same, retrolateral view. Scale lines: 1.0mm (C), 0.5mm (A, B, E–G), 0.2mm (D)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5317618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5317618/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
), from 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D14FFC2FF88FA044CB4FF78FCEF" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="manueli">
<emphasis id="B905EA85FFC2FF88FA044CB4FF78FCEF" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">P. manueli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the shape of tip of the procursus and the larger appendix of the bulb (
<figureCitation id="134A2A12FFC2FF88FBC84D4FFB5DFCEE" box="[1098,1235,785,811]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="15.[151,255,1887,1911]" captionTargetBox="[256,1339,226,1852]" captionTargetId="figure-78@15.[244,1352,194,1880]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 3. Pholcus bessus Zhu &amp; Gong, 1991 (illustrations modified from Zhu &amp; Gong 1991). A. epigynum, ventral view. B. same, dorsal view. C. male prosoma, dorsal view. D. trochanter of male left palp, retrolaterodorsal view. E. male left chelicera, frontal view. F. left palp, prolateral view. G. same, retrolateral view. Scale lines: 1.0mm (C), 0.5mm (A, B, E–G), 0.2mm (D)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5317618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5317618/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Figs. 3F–G</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36B651CFFC2FF88FF444D69FB22FA26" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCE3697FFC2FF88FF444D69FC9EFB3E" blockId="14.[151,1436,591,1700]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis id="B905EA85FFC2FF88FF444D69FEF2FC94" bold="true" box="[198,380,823,849]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Redescription.</emphasis>
Male (
<typeStatus id="54CA8835FFC2FF88FE4F4D66FDB7FC97" box="[461,569,824,850]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">holotype</typeStatus>
), total length 3.6: cephalothorax 1.1 long, 1.3 wide; abdomen 2.5 long, 1.3 wide. Leg I: 36.1 (9.2+0.6+9.4+14.6+2.3), tibia II: 6.5, tibia III: 4.2, tibia IV: 5.8; Tibia I L/D: 72. Prosoma shape as in 
<figureCitation id="134A2A12FFC2FF88FEA44DDBFE0AFC5A" box="[294,388,901,927]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="15.[151,255,1887,1911]" captionTargetBox="[256,1339,226,1852]" captionTargetId="figure-78@15.[244,1352,194,1880]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 3. Pholcus bessus Zhu &amp; Gong, 1991 (illustrations modified from Zhu &amp; Gong 1991). A. epigynum, ventral view. B. same, dorsal view. C. male prosoma, dorsal view. D. trochanter of male left palp, retrolaterodorsal view. E. male left chelicera, frontal view. F. left palp, prolateral view. G. same, retrolateral view. Scale lines: 1.0mm (C), 0.5mm (A, B, E–G), 0.2mm (D)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5317618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5317618/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
. Carapace short, broad and almost circular, ochre, with brown butterfly-shaped marks broadly connecting to ocular area. Cephalic region clothed with short, erect and black hairs, without brown marks centrally; ocular area light yellow. Clypeus 0.40, unmodified, slightly ochre, without yellow marks. Distance AME–AME 0.03. Diameter AME 0.07, ALE 0.15, PME 0.15, PLE 0.15. Chelicerae as in 
<figureCitation id="134A2A12FFC2FF88FABE4DA7FA19FBD6" box="[1340,1431,1017,1043]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="15.[151,255,1887,1911]" captionTargetBox="[256,1339,226,1852]" captionTargetId="figure-78@15.[244,1352,194,1880]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 3. Pholcus bessus Zhu &amp; Gong, 1991 (illustrations modified from Zhu &amp; Gong 1991). A. epigynum, ventral view. B. same, dorsal view. C. male prosoma, dorsal view. D. trochanter of male left palp, retrolaterodorsal view. E. male left chelicera, frontal view. F. left palp, prolateral view. G. same, retrolateral view. Scale lines: 1.0mm (C), 0.5mm (A, B, E–G), 0.2mm (D)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5317618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5317618/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
, with pair of black serrated apophyses distally, pair of unsclerotized thumb-shaped apophyses proximolaterally and pair of small unsclerotized rounded apophyses proximocentrally. Labium light yellow. Sternum longer than wide, yellow, with three pairs of gray patches laterally and a mark centrally. Femora, patellae and tibiae ochre, with dark rings, metatarsi and tarsi brown. Abdomen cylindrical, pale ochre, dorsum with numerous blackish marks. Venter pale brown. Palps as in 
<figureCitation id="134A2A12FFC2FF88FD574AE4FC19FB11" box="[725,919,1210,1236]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="15.[151,255,1887,1911]" captionTargetBox="[256,1339,226,1852]" captionTargetId="figure-78@15.[244,1352,194,1880]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 3. Pholcus bessus Zhu &amp; Gong, 1991 (illustrations modified from Zhu &amp; Gong 1991). A. epigynum, ventral view. B. same, dorsal view. C. male prosoma, dorsal view. D. trochanter of male left palp, retrolaterodorsal view. E. male left chelicera, frontal view. F. left palp, prolateral view. G. same, retrolateral view. Scale lines: 1.0mm (C), 0.5mm (A, B, E–G), 0.2mm (D)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5317618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5317618/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Figs. 3F and 3G</figureCitation>
, bulb with a curved uncus and a triangular appendix, femur with a small projection retrolaterally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCE3697FFC2FF88FF444B59FF74FA8D" blockId="14.[151,1436,591,1700]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis id="B905EA85FFC2FF88FF444B59FEC8FAE4" bold="true" box="[198,326,1287,1313]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Variation.</emphasis>
Tibia I in two other males: 8.8, 9.1. Body color in 
<typeStatus id="54CA8835FFC2FF88FC3A4B56FB90FAE7" box="[952,1054,1288,1314]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">holotype</typeStatus>
deeper than in other males and females.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCE3697FFC2FF88FF444B0BFB22FA26" blockId="14.[151,1436,591,1700]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Female: in general very similar to male. Total body length 4.3–4.4. Female (‘allotype’), total length 4.4: cephalothorax 1.2 long, 1.3 wide; abdomen 3.2 long, 2.6 wide. Tibia I 5.6 (in other female missing). Epigynum roughly rectangular as in 
<figureCitation id="134A2A12FFC2FF88FDC64BFDFD11FA78" box="[580,671,1443,1469]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="15.[151,255,1887,1911]" captionTargetBox="[256,1339,226,1852]" captionTargetId="figure-78@15.[244,1352,194,1880]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 3. Pholcus bessus Zhu &amp; Gong, 1991 (illustrations modified from Zhu &amp; Gong 1991). A. epigynum, ventral view. B. same, dorsal view. C. male prosoma, dorsal view. D. trochanter of male left palp, retrolaterodorsal view. E. male left chelicera, frontal view. F. left palp, prolateral view. G. same, retrolateral view. Scale lines: 1.0mm (C), 0.5mm (A, B, E–G), 0.2mm (D)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5317618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5317618/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
, with a knob-shaped apophysis on the top. Dorsal view as in 
<figureCitation id="134A2A12FFC2FF88FAEF4BFDFF35FA26" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="15.[151,255,1887,1911]" captionTargetBox="[256,1339,226,1852]" captionTargetId="figure-78@15.[244,1352,194,1880]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 3. Pholcus bessus Zhu &amp; Gong, 1991 (illustrations modified from Zhu &amp; Gong 1991). A. epigynum, ventral view. B. same, dorsal view. C. male prosoma, dorsal view. D. trochanter of male left palp, retrolaterodorsal view. E. male left chelicera, frontal view. F. left palp, prolateral view. G. same, retrolateral view. Scale lines: 1.0mm (C), 0.5mm (A, B, E–G), 0.2mm (D)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5317618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5317618/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
, with a broad V-shaped sclerotized arch anteriorly and a pair of large oval pore plates.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
